&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.1em; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180466/rss" title="piccalil.li" style=" color: #3366aa;    font-size: 1.05em;"&gt;It‚Äôs About to Get a Lot Easier For Your JavaScript to Clean Up After¬†Itself&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî A fun technical exploration of &lt;code&gt;Symbol.dispose&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;using&lt;/code&gt;, two new features that‚Äôll ease many headaches around cleaning up after yourself: closing connections, freeing resources, etc. Just watch out for the¬†Muppets‚Ä¶&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Mat Marquis &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.1em; color: #000;"&gt;‚ñ∂¬†¬†&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180467/rss" title="www.youtube.com" style=" color: #3366aa;    font-size: 1.05em;"&gt;Evan You on Vite, Rust and the Future of JS¬†Tooling&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî The Vue.js creator joined the Better Stack podcast to discuss his path from building Vite to founding VoidZero and developing a Rust-based JS toolchain.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Evan You and Better Stack &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.1em; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180468/rss" title="blog.sentry.io" style=" color: #3366aa;    font-size: 1.05em;"&gt;Debugging a Next.js Production Issue with Sentry Logs, Not Just¬†Errors&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî Lessons from a Next.js production debugging session where understanding behavior mattered more than stack¬†traces.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Sentry &lt;span style="text-transform: uppercase; margin-left: 4px; font-size: 0.9em;   color: #993 !important; padding-top: 1px; padding-right: 4px;  padding-left: 4px;            "&gt;sponsor&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.1em; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;ü§ñ&lt;/span&gt;¬†&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180469/rss" title="www.developerway.com" style=" color: #3366aa;    font-size: 1.05em;"&gt;Debugging React with AI: Can It Replace an Experienced Developer?&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî Nadia rigged up an app laced with subtle bugs, unleashed Claude on it, and‚Ä¶ watched it fail to¬†impress.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Nadia Makarevich &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;üìÑ &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180470/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;Why Inngest Migrated from Next.js to TanStack Start&lt;/a&gt; &lt;cite&gt;Jacob Heric&lt;/cite&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;üìÑ &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180471/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;Implementing the Temporal Proposal in JavaScriptCore&lt;/a&gt; &lt;cite&gt;Tim Chevalier (Igalia)&lt;/cite&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;üìÑ &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180472/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;What to Expect in Angular 22&lt;/a&gt;  &lt;cite&gt;Kelly Vatter (Mescius)&lt;/cite&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;üìÑ &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180473/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;Solid.js Best Practices&lt;/a&gt;  &lt;cite&gt;Brenley Dueck&lt;/cite&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0; padding-right: 0;  padding-left: 0;"&gt;&lt;p&gt;üõ†¬†Code &amp;amp; Tools&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.1em; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180474/rss" title="shovel.js.org" style=" color: #3366aa;    font-size: 1.05em;"&gt;Shovel.js: What If Your Server Were Just a Service¬†Worker?&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî A full-stack framework and meta-framework built around the &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180475/rss" style=" color: #3366aa;   "&gt;Service Worker&lt;/a&gt; model, using Web APIs wherever possible to provide a consistent server surface across Node, Bun, and edge runtimes.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Brian Kim &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.1em; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180476/rss" title="verifyfetch.com" style=" color: #3366aa;    font-size: 1.05em;"&gt;VerifyFetch: Fetch Large Files with Resume and Verification¬†Features&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî Imagine &lt;code&gt;fetch&lt;/code&gt; but with the ability to resume downloads, check you downloaded what you meant to download, and fail fast on any corruption. &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180477/rss" style=" color: #3366aa;   "&gt;GitHub¬†repo.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
