&lt;p&gt;üò¨ &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180494/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;Heroku&lt;/a&gt;, the cloud hosting/PaaS pioneer, has &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180495/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;adopted a 'sustaining engineering model'&lt;/a&gt;, with no new features in the pipeline. The dev community &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180496/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;heard the 'death rattle'&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;code&gt;migrate off heroku&lt;/code&gt; has joined many to-do¬†lists.&lt;/p&gt;
