  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.1em; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/179827/rss" title="dev.to" style=" color: #3366aa;    font-size: 1.05em;"&gt;JavaScript Frameworks ‚Äì Heading into 2026&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî The creator of &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/179828/rss" style=" color: #3366aa;   "&gt;SolidJS&lt;/a&gt; knows more than a thing or two about JS frameworks and has written an annual review of the scene for the past few years. Here, he picks on four areas of evolution, and says it‚Äôs &lt;em&gt;‚Äúan incredibly exciting time to be working on JavaScript¬†frameworks.‚Äù&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
