&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;üîé The VS Code team has put together a fascinating blog post about &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/179494/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;how they implemented a new, fast client-side docs search system&lt;/a&gt; for the VS Code site using Rust and WebAssembly. You can use their &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/179495/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;docfind engine&lt;/a&gt; for yourself too, and &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/179496/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;there's a live demo here&lt;/a&gt; showing off how fast it is over an index of 50,000 news¬†articles.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;üìä &lt;em&gt;HTTP Archive&lt;/em&gt; has released its &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/179497/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;latest &lt;em&gt;Web Almanac&lt;/em&gt; for 2025&lt;/a&gt; packed with raw stats, trends, and observations about the state of the Web over the past year, covering areas like &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/179498/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;WebAssembly&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/179499/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;performance&lt;/a&gt;, and ever-increasing &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/179500/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;page¬†weight&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A developer makes &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/179501/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;a prediction that Microsoft will eventually discontinue Windows&lt;/a&gt; in favor of a Windows-themed Linux distribution.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Things are &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/179502/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;not looking good for the MySQL project.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
